            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong>, a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for a further 4 min or until the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a ragù-like consistency</p><p>Note: Please make sure you cook your pork mince thoroughly (until piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
